content.review:
The authors of this manuscript transformed the k-mer representation of DNA fragments to a 2D image representation using the space-filling Hilbert curves for the classification of chromatin occupancy. In generally, this paper is easy to read. The components of the proposed model mainly include Hilbert curve theory and CNN which are existing technologies. But the authors make their combination useful in applications. Some specific comments are:

1. In page 5, I could not understand the formula d_kink < d_out. d_link ;
2. There may exist some new histone modification data that were captured by the next-generation sequencing (e.g. ChIP-seq) and are more accurate;  
3. It seems that the authors treat it as a two-class problem for each data set. It would be more useful in real applications if all the data sets are combined to form a multi-class problem.

